description:
GOAL: Driver fn that runs the two single-pass functions to fixpoint with
GROWTH_CAP enforcement, and wire it into compile_with_backend after
rewrite_known_target_closures.

Parent: fz-ul4.11.15. Depends on: fz-ul4.11.15.3.

## Deliverables (extend src/ir_inline.rs)

  /// Iterate the two passes to fixpoint or MAX_ITERATIONS, whichever comes
  /// first. Enforces GROWTH_CAP per fn: track each fn's stmt_count BEFORE
  /// the first iteration; during each rewrite, if the candidate post-rewrite
  /// stmt_count would exceed 4x the pre-pass baseline for that caller fn,
  /// reject THAT individual rewrite (skip the site, continue with others).
  /// Returns total rewrites performed across all iterations.
  pub fn inline_module(m: &mut Module) -> usize;

  Pass order per iteration:
    1. inline_tail_calls_once(m)
    2. inline_calls_once(m)

  Rationale: two-pass (TailCall first, then Call+Cont). After
  rewrite_known_target_closures has already run, no closure-resolution pass
  is needed here.

## GROWTH_CAP implementation

  Before iteration loop:
    let baseline: HashMap<FnId, usize> =
        m.fns.iter().map(|f| (f.id, stmt_count(f))).collect();

  Each rewrite candidate site computes a hypothetical post-stmt-count for the
  caller (caller_baseline + callee_stmts). If > 4 * baseline[caller.id],
  reject this site. Per-site rejection — does NOT halt the iteration.

  Note: baseline is fixed at the start; we do NOT recompute it after each
  iteration. This means the cap is "4x of the ORIGINAL fn size", not
  "4x of last iteration." Intentional: prevents 4 x 4 x 4 = 64x blowup
  across iterations.

## Pipeline integration

  src/ir_codegen.rs compile_with_backend current sequence (ir_codegen.rs:1896-1908):

    let mut working = module.clone();
    let pre_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    crate::ir_typer::rewrite_vec_kinds(&mut working, &pre_types)?;
    let mid_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    crate::ir_typer::rewrite_known_target_closures(&mut working, &mid_types);
    let module_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    // ... per-fn compile loop ...

  New sequence (insert after rewrite_known_target_closures):

    let mut working = module.clone();
    let pre_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    crate::ir_typer::rewrite_vec_kinds(&mut working, &pre_types)?;
    let mid_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    crate::ir_typer::rewrite_known_target_closures(&mut working, &mid_types);
    ir_inline::inline_module(&mut working);   // <-- new
    let module_types = crate::ir_typer::type_module(&working);
    // ... per-fn compile loop ...

  Also add `mod ir_inline;` in src/main.rs (after `mod ir_codegen;`).

  Insertion point rationale: rewrite_known_target_closures has already
  converted known-target CallClosure/TailCallClosure to direct Call/TailCall,
  expanding the set of inlinable call sites. The final type_module runs after
  inlining, so the typer sees fused bodies.

## Tests

  - Chain inline: hand-built A tail-calls B tail-calls C, all leaves; after
    inline_module, A's body has no TailCall to B or C.
  - Fixpoint terminates: pathological case (no inlinable sites) returns 0.
  - MAX_ITERATIONS cap: synthetic test that demonstrates the loop stops at 3
    rounds even when more inlining is theoretically possible.
  - GROWTH_CAP engages: caller with 4 stmts; callee with 5 stmts; 10
    callsites in caller; without cap caller would balloon to 4+50=54 stmts.
    With cap=4 (max 16 stmts), only the first few sites inline.
  - End-to-end: run existing fixture set through `fz run`; assert same
    output as pre-inline baseline. Full test suite must not regress.

## Risks

  - Inserting inliner after rewrite_known_target_closures but before final
    type_module means the typer sees inlined bodies. The typer is flow-
    sensitive but provenance-agnostic, so semantically equivalent code
    produces equivalent types. Mitigation: full test suite must pass.

## Acceptance

  - cargo test passes (no regressions).
  - New inliner-driver tests pass.
  - `fz run` still works on existing fixtures.
  - One commit referencing fz-ul4.11.15.5.

## References

  - src/ir_codegen.rs:1896-1908 (pipeline sequence to modify).
  - fz-ul4.29.10.3 (rewrite_known_target_closures — runs just before inline).
